Here's someone who's just fixing my kitchen floor. And I'm acting as if I still have a job and work from home while I'm sitting on Too Hot to Handle.
If I could damn it open the file. (Damn One Drive.)
*Voice of a Hacker* I'm in.
And that's exactly when he starts drilling super loudly. Yay.
It feels uncomfortably passive-aggressive to crank my air purifier to the max, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would even be completely okay, even if he weren't a mask opponent. And do I really have to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't until he's gone.
At least I've finally finished revising Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damn terrifying. Oh yeah, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing search and replace for … ➡️ ellipsis symbol and there are 54 of them in this chapter 😅
But no, I stand by my statement. Natural language is usually fragmented, especially when one becomes emotional.
The handyman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he'll be done soon.
He went out to cut something (it sounds like that at least). I secretly checked how far he is, and there's still a lot to do :(
7 pages left in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's pretty much neat – mostly changes to the font and very small corrections in direct speech, and I need to make everything a bit more concise. But I really could use a break and a cup of tea right now, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he's just started vacuuming again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me he had made a cost estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were stingy and only paid for the part next to the door that's no longer in order. It feels much better now.
The house is being aired out, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I'm drinking tea in the garden!
